HEADWORD: Lycopodiaceous
<hw>Ly`co*po`di*a"ceous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Belonging, or relating, to the
<ord>Lycopodiace⟦ae⟧</ord>, an order of cryptogamous plants (called also
<altname>club mosses</altname>) with branching stems, and small,
crowded, one-nerved, and usually pointed leaves.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

